CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 9, 1950, pg. 17 reads: "Shut-Ins Remembered at Leech Farm - More than 450 patients were recently made happy when representatives from the Young People's Department of the Women's Missionary Society made, and presented to them, favors.  The group has been distributing the tokens of good will for four years...Right: Members of the group present some of the gifts to Nurse Cronin.  Pictured, left to right: Mrs. Elsie Meeks, Misses Gladys Miller, Myrna Miller, Patricia Miller, Margrettia Hartaway, Dorothy Patton, Mary Archie and Margaret Bennett...-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Members of Young People's Department of the Women's Missionary Society, from left: Elsie Meeks, recipient of gifts Nurse Cronin, Gladys Miller, Myrna Miller, Patricia Miller, Margrettia Hartaway, Dorothy Patton, Mary Archie, and Margaret Bennett, standing in Leech Farm
